Advance Xpath Method:

1. Parent : identify the partent with the help chid element.
            e.g.  //tagname[@attribute='value']/parent::tagname[attribute='value']
            e.g.  //input[@value='radio_123']/parent::li


2. Ancestor : identify the grand parent with the help of grand child.
            e.g -> //input[@value='radio_123']/ancestor::div[@align="left"]


3. following : identify all the elementwhich are available below the referance element on webpage/DOM structure
            e.g -> //input[@id='fromcity']//following::input



4. following-sibling : identity the sibling elements which is available below to referance sibling element

                e.g -> //td[text()='Kolkata']//following-sibling::td[text()='5000']



5. preceding : identify all the elementwhich are available below the referance element on webpage/DOM structure
                e.g -> //input[@id='fromcity']//preceding::input



6. preceding-sibling : identity the sibling elements which is available above to referance sibling element

                e.g -> //td[text()='Kolkata']//preceding-sibling::td


